HEADWORD: Cacoon
<hw>Ca*coon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the seeds or
large beans of a tropical vine (<spn>Entada scandens</spn>) used for
making purses, scent bottles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

